  "text": "Then, we compute the reference conductivity fieldκ(x) as a realization of Eq [CITATION_1] and solve Eq (25) with the finite element method to obtain the reference solution,û(x). Next, we select N κ values ofκ(x) and N u values ofû(x) as measurements of these fields and reconstructκ(x) asκ(x, ξ * ) by solving the minimization problem [CITATION_2] . The conditioned surrogate modelũ C in (24) is constructed by solving Eq (25) with the finite element method at collocation points. In the finite element solutions, the domain is discretized with 256 equal size elements. We study the relative error of the inferred conductivityκ(x, ξ * ),",
